Activity: A29 - Find a publicly available AI-generated image, video, or audio clip, use at least one detection or verification tool to analyse it

Objective
The goal of this activity was to identify and analyse an AI-generated image using detection tools to verify its authenticity.

Method
I selected an AI-generated image of a cat in space wearing an astronaut suit. Then, I used an online detection tool (such as AI Image Detector or Hive Moderation) to examine the image. I checked for visual artefacts, metadata inconsistencies, and other indicators that the content was synthetically created.

Findings
1. The image showed subtle inconsistencies in textures and shapes, particularly in areas like the cat’s suit edges and the background stars.
2. Metadata analysis suggested synthetic creation due to missing or unusual camera information.
3. The detection tool returned a high probability that the image was AI-generated, confirming suspicions based on visual inspection.

Security Principle
This activity relates to integrity, as detecting AI-generated content helps prevent misinformation, impersonation, and manipulation online.

Evidence
- photos in evidence folder

Reflection
This activity helped me understand how convincing AI-generated images can be and the importance of using verification tools. Recognising synthetic content is crucial in cybersecurity to prevent the spread of misinformation and maintain trust in digital media.
